iginally a warrior's nickname, composed of <i>tan</i> ‘fire’ and <i>ki</i> ‘dog’. This surname is also found in Britain. Compare   Tanguay  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Tingey","meanings":["Cornish: from the Breton personal name <i>Tangi</i>, <i>Tanguy</i> (see   Tanguy  )."]},{"name":"Tanguay","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Adrien, Marcel, Andre, Normand, Armand, Gaston, Gilles, Pierre, Alphonse, Herve, Lucien, Michel.","Altered form of Breton   Tanguy  .","History: Bearers of the surname <i>Tanguay</i> trace their origin to Jean Tanguy/Tanguay <i>dit</i> La Navette from Ploudiry in Finistère, Brittany, who married Marie Brochu in Saint-Jean, Île d'Orléans, QC, in 1692."]}]},{"name":"Marie","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Maria .  When first introduced to England in the Middle Ages, it was Anglicized in pronunciation and respelled   Mary .  This French form was reintroduced into the English-speaking world as a separate name in the 19th century, and is still pronounced more or less in the French manner, although sometimes with the stress on the first syllable. It is now often used in combination with other names such as <i>Ellie</i>, <i>Chloe</i>, and <i>Lisa</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Marie DE TANGRY was born in 1065, in Tangry, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, her father, Wallerand II DE TANGRY, was 29 and her mother, Marie Louise DE NEDONCHEL, was 19. She married Louis DE BLINGEL in 1080. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1098, in Blingel, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, at the age of 33."},"et":{"1065–1098":"1065–1098","1061–1121":"1061–1121","1068–1109":"1068–1109","1059–1114":"1059–1114","1082–1135":"1082–1135","1084–1142":"1084–1142","1036–1098":"1036–1098","1046–1102":"1046–1102","1080":"1080","1121":"1121","1065":"1065","1098":"1098","1142":"1142","1064":"1064","1084":"108